Project description

CuPy : NumPy & SciPy for GPU

CuPy is a NumPy/SciPy-compatible array library for GPU-accelerated computing with Python.

This is a CuPy wheel (precompiled binary) package for CUDA 10.2.You need to install CUDA Toolkit 10.2 to use these packages.

If you have another version of CUDA, or want to build from source, refer to the Installation Guide for instructions.
